x4freetext: D-T neutron source
The active area of 25 mm2 and thickness 100 mu-m
Both the aluminium thick sheets were removed
from the chamber and the activity of 0.84 MeV gamma
rays emitted by 27Mg produced through the 27Al(n,p)27Mg
reaction, with half-life 9.5 minutes was measured using
a HPGe detector for neutron flux monitoring
Detection of alpha particles
incident deuteron energy ~175keV
The neutron flux was kept around 10**5 neutrons/cm2/sec
on the nickel or aluminium scattering foil
For neutron flux
measurement
an error 10% to the cross-section also
appears from the statistics and uncertainty in
estimating the total cross-section from the least
square fittings in addition to DATA-ERR2
The uncertainty contributions to the
cross- section are mainly from the errors in:
the target thickness 2.5%,
neutron flux 2%,
neutron energy spread 0.01%,
distances between the tritium target to
aluminium or nickel foil, distance between the
scattering foil and the SSB detector 0.25%,
solid angle subtended by the detector 1%,
counts due to the contributions from the
background charged particles 2%
and energy calibration of the detector 0.5%.
All these errors are added in quadrature.
Tables from the author B.Lalremruata
